Tragedy struck on Suncoast Beach on Saturday morning when a 21-year-old man was killed after a tree stump rolled on to him. According to ER24 spokesperson, Ineke van Huyssteen, when ER paramedics arrived on the scene at 1:30am, the man was found lying underneath the tree stump on the beach. “It is believed that the tree stump was on top of an embankment before it came loose and rolled down on top of the man.
Unfortunately, there was nothing they could do for him and he was declared dead on the scene by ER24. The exact circumstances of the incident will be further investigated by authorities who responded to the scene.”